2011-08-12T14:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/u-s-june-business-inventories-and-sales-report-text-.html
The following is the text of the
retail sales and inventories by business from the Commerce
Department.  MANUFACTURING AND TRADE INVENTORIES AND SALES
June 2011  Sales.
The U.S. Census Bureau announced today that the combined value of
distributive trade sales and manufacturers' shipments for May,
adjusted for seasonal and trading-day differences but not for
price changes, was estimated at $1,187.8 billion, up 0.4 percent
from May 2011 and up 12.4 percent from June 2010.  Inventories.
Manufacturers' and trade inventories, adjusted for seasonal
variations but not for price changes, were estimated at an end-of-
month level of $1,518.5 billion, up 0.3 percent from May 2011 and
up 11.1 percent from June 2010.  Inventories/Sales Ratio.
The total business inventories/sales ratio based on seasonally
adjusted data at the end of June was 1.28. The June 2010 ratio
was 1.29.  SOURCE: U.S. Commerce Department.  http://www.census.gov/bussales   To contact the reporter on this story:
